    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-12-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="561"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                <head>No. 561.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Neill</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-12-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 22, 1886</date>. (Received January 8,
                        1887.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 189.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge receipt of your
                    communication No. 112, dated November 30, 1886, as being in receipt of dispatch
                    No. 171, of the 28th of October last, from this legation, in reference to an act
                    of the Peruvian Congress, declaring null and void all “interior acts” of the
                    Pierola and Iglesias governments.</p>
                <p>I beg leave to state that the “decree” appeared in “El Comercio” of the 21st
                    instant, signed by the President, Andres A. Caceres, and by Manuel Velarde, the
                    then minister of government, and dated the 26th of October, 1886.</p>
                <p>I have etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard R. Neill.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
